Information reaching Phakaaathi has revealed that Mamelodi Sundowns winger, Phakamani Mahlambi, who is currently on loan at Chippa United, is most likely to be without a team at the end of the season. READ ALSO: Pirates to lose flaming Mhango following stellar Afcon? His loan expires at the end of the season and Chippa are giving him the benefit of a doubt to see if he will improve in the remainder of the DStv Premiership. Meanwhile, Downs are said to not be wanting him back and as soon as he returns from loan, he will be shown the door. Chippa are believed to have extended an olive branch to the former Al-Ahly player as they were considering to prematurely terminate his loan deal.